text: Thryptomene pinifolia is a shrub species in the family Myrtaceae that is endemic to Western Australia. The shrub is found in the Mid West region of Western Australia around Northampton. ==References== pinifolia Category:Endemic flora of Western Australia Category:Rosids of Western Australia Category:Vulnerable flora of Australia Category:Plants described in 2014 Category:Taxa named by Barbara Lynette Rye Category:Taxa named by Malcolm Eric Trudgen
